rComments: Djerboua is a good person in general but his course is so boring, he tries to remedy that but he doesn't succeed too much. The case studies are very easy but the intra and final are not. You really have to work hard to get a good grade in your course. For him, as long as a student does well on the exam, everyone else could do it. He doesn't listen

Doesn't post the slides, recordings are only posted for 24h after the lecture. Boring class taught by a decent prof, but he didn't make much effort to make it entertaining, so a 7-10 slot every week is a grind to get through. all 5 case studies are easy marks, pay attention and take good notes and you'll be fine.

This Prof marks very generously and the midterm was fair. By no means are his classes easy, but if you put the work in you can do well. He tried to make the lectures as interesting as possible despite how boring sometimes the material was. To help you do well, make sure to read the textbook as well.

Hes one of the rudest profs Ive had. He gave us a midterm, 1.5 hrs, 4 long case studies, on top of that T/F and MC. i asked to see my grade and asked why I got a lower grade. He told me "the exam was attainable for everyone who worked hard enough". he then told me that "you are not very familiar with organizing your time with cases"

Gives 4 case studies with 3 questions each in a 1.5 hour midterm alongside multiple choice, short answer & T/F. He is such a tough grader for someone who has half their work in French and the other half in English. Would never take again.
November 15, a month left of classes and still not a single grade received. This professor is disorganized, doesn't answer to emails and is quite rude. DO NOT TAKE HIM NO MATTER WHAT.
The midterm was impossible given the amount time. Lectures are dry, and the prof is impatient.

extremely boring and monotone. i was falling asleep during all the lectures. unorganized and the instructions are a bizarre combination of french and english which he doesn't bother to correct. he's so defensive despite asking for feedback. i didn't expect this class to be as hard as it was.

He creates genuinely the most difficult and dismissive class I've ever taken. He makes 50% of your final mark a group project that is just him posting dozens of files on brightspace, some english and some french, and vague instructions. He creates an atmosphere where you are punished for asking questions and belittled. Doesnt record lectures.

one of the worst profs i ever had. took this course as an elective because i thought it was easy and regret it. he is boring, slow, and never gets to the point. I honestly don't understand how he got the rating that he has. he turned a very easy course into a nightmare. Overall i would not recommend

Absolutely love his lectures, his class was probably one of my favorite classes. The way he interacts with the class and makes his lectures super interactive is admirable. The course has group projects and assignments for which reading the textbook is super important. Reading and doing the mini group assignments efficiently is recommended.
Doesn't really have a unique teaching style, but an easy grader.
Class could have been more engaging, but Djerboua did a well enough job in turning a very dry topic into a mediocre lecture. Cases aren't graded too tough. Midterm was fair.

The lectures are incredibly dry and uninteresting, he just speaks at you and its all over the place. You need to be extremely specific with your answers for graded work/tests. If you go to ask him questions about the in class cases or midterms, he doesn't even answer your questions what so ever. You are better off to follow the textbook.
Great, sweet and funny prof. Tries to engage people during the 3 hour-long class, and thanks to him it is, although still boring, not as boring as other 7 to 10 lectures!
Great lecturer and always willing to answer questions and make sure everything is clear!
